No, tensorflow is not supported and does not work out of the box on 32-bit desktop operating systems.
You can probably make it work by building from sources, but you need to reach out to the community in stackoverflow for support with issues on that.

body:
No, tensorflow is not supported and does not work out of the box on 32-bit desktop operating systems.
You can probably make it work by building from sources, but you need to reach out to the community in stackoverflow for support with issues on that.
